    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>ESPN Golf Analyst Leaves for NBC</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By RICHARD SANDOMIR</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Sandomir, Richard</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Jimmy Roberts to leave ESPN as golf analyst to join NBC in time for US Open (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Jimmy Roberts, one of the leading correspondents at ESPN, is joining NBC Sports next month in time for the United States Open golf championship.</p>
        <p>Roberts, whose specialty at ESPN was golf reporting and essays, will be covering golf, tennis, horse racing and the Olympics for NBC.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Jimmy Roberts, one of the leading correspondents at ESPN, is joining NBC Sports next month in time for the United States Open golf championship.</p>
        <p>Roberts, whose specialty at ESPN was golf reporting and essays, will be covering golf, tennis, horse racing and the Olympics for NBC.</p>
        <p>Dick Ebersol came to me and said, ''I want you to be our essayist, our voice,''  Roberts said, referring to the chairman of NBC Sports. Storytelling is very important to him and that's what I do.</p>
        <p>Roberts had been a producer and writer for ABC Sports and ABC News before being hired by ESPN in 1988. ''I feel very committed to ESPN because they were the first to put me on the air,'' he said. He has won 13 Sports Emmys.</p>
        <p>RICHARD SANDOMIR</p>
        <p>PLUS: BROADCASTING</p>
      </block>
